instNote: ﻿Rev. F. Pierz is now engaged in establishing some missions amongst the Chippeway Indians...These missions promise to be very successful, on account of the good dispositions of these Indians, who have several times expressed their wishes to have some black gowns among them.  The same success could be expected among the Sioux, the Assinibaines and the other tribes of this diocese, should some other clergymen come to devote themselves to such missions, and should also any pecuniary means be granted to support them.
